=======================================================
  LAVANYA OMS v5 — VERCEL DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
=======================================================

STEP 1: PUSH TO GITHUB
-----------------------
git init
git add .
git commit -m "v5 vercel deploy"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/lavanya-oms.git
git push -u origin main


STEP 2: IMPORT TO VERCEL
-------------------------
1. Go to https://vercel.com → "Add New Project"
2. Import your GitHub repo
3. Framework: Vite (auto-detected)
4. Build Command:    npm run build
5. Output Directory: dist
6. Click "Deploy" — do NOT touch environment variables yet


STEP 3: ADD ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (CRITICAL)
---------------------------------------------
After first deploy, go to:
  Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables

Add BOTH of these:

  Key:   VITE_SUPABASE_URL
  Value: https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
  (Find this in: Supabase → Your Project → Settings → API → Project URL)

  Key:   VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
  Value: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
  (Find this in: Supabase → Your Project → Settings → API → anon public)

  ⚠️  The "VITE_" prefix is MANDATORY. Without it, the browser
      cannot read these values and Supabase will not connect.

After adding both variables → click "Redeploy" (Deployments tab → ••• → Redeploy)


STEP 4: CUSTOM DOMAIN
----------------------
Vercel → Project → Settings → Domains → Add your domain
Copy the CNAME or A record shown → add it in your domain registrar's DNS settings
SSL certificate is automatic (5–10 minutes)


WHAT WAS FIXED IN THIS ZIP
----------------------------
1. package.json   — Removed Electron/desktop dependencies (electron,
                    electron-builder, concurrently, wait-on, main.js entry).
                    These caused Vercel build failures. All React logic
                    and Supabase code is 100% unchanged.

2. vite.config.js — Changed base from './' to '/' so asset paths
                    resolve correctly on Vercel's CDN.

No component logic, no Supabase integration, no UI was changed.
